He delivered a message of honesty, tolerance, love, environmental awareness and social consciousness The Jamia Arabia graduate in Raiwind was on a one-week lecture tour of South Africa. A prominent leader of the Tablighi Jamaat, Jameel is listed as one of the 500 most influential Islamic personalities. He is distinguished for his Arabic and Urdu oratory and is highly appreciated for his message of peace, tolerance, moderation, love and respect. He focuses on introspection, self-correction, social consciousness and avoidance of violence. He has had a tremendous impact on several personalities ranging from former cricket superstar Imran Khan, politicians such as Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif to actress and radio personality Veena Malik. During his tour, he addressed huge audiences at the Gallagher Convention Centre in Johannesburg and Orient Hall in Durban. 